aacte presents pam grossman with the outstanding journal of teacher education article award stanford university school of education skip to main content skip to main navigation stanford university school of education home suse directory library axess make a gift stanford home search this site about suse admissions academics faculty & research news & events knowledge at work home news & events press releases aacte presents pam grossman with the outstanding journal of teacher education article award aacte presents pam grossman with the outstanding journal of teacher education article award tweet february 6 2009 american association of colleges for teacher education media contact alyssa mangino amangino aacte org 202 478 4596 chicago il the american association of colleges for teacher education aacte has selected an article by pam grossman of stanford university to receive the 2009 outstanding journal of teacher education article award the award will be presented on saturday february 7 during the wilbur j cohen lecture at the association's 61st annual meeting and exhibits in chicago illinois the award sponsored by aacte's committee on research and dissemination along with sage publications recognizes exemplary scholarship published in the journal of teacher education jte in the areas of teacher education or of teaching and learning implications for teacher education the article responding to our critics from crisis to opportunity in research on teacher education published in the january february 2008 issue of jte uses andrew abbott's concept of jurisdictional challenge to analyze the current problems facing university based teacher educators the article theorizes that teacher educators are far too close to losing authority over the preparation of new professionals and the production of academic knowledge for the profession the piece details the need for teacher education researchers to respond to such jurisdictional challenges by focusing on pressing policy issues regarding the preparation of teachers and by strengthening the quality of research not only was this article well written but it makes an important contribution to the field acclaimed the aacte selection committee in particular it challenges those of us in the field of teacher education to come to terms with and make changes in the ways in which we conduct research on teacher education our ability to improve the quality of research is essential given the current context surrounding teacher education and this article raises the bar for more information please contact alyssa mangino aacte communications manager at amangino aacte org or 202.478 4596 aacte serving learners the american association of colleges for teacher education is a national alliance of educator preparation programs dedicated to the highest quality professional development of teachers and school leaders in order to enhance pk 12 student learning the 800 institutions holding aacte membership represent public and private colleges and universities in every state the district of columbia the virgin islands puerto rico and guam aacte's reach and influence fuel its mission of serving learners by providing all school personnel with superior training and continuing education news &amp events events in the spotlight school news press releases suse in the media stanford educator itunes u suse on youtube press releases professor ari y kelman appointed inaugural jim joseph chair in education and jewish studies at stanford november 21 2011 school of education and jim joseph foundation in the 2000s family income segregation grew greatly in nearly all us metro areas november 16 2011 us2010 stanford ramps up efforts to recruit and prepare k 12 math and science teachers october 12 2011 school of education news adolescence experts discuss teen health optimal school success september 8 2011 school of education news stanford launches effort to improve english language learner access to common core state standards august 15 